<body>
    <h1>HttpCache</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"HttpCache-ContentCache">Content Cache</h1>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message problem shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Limitation</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-problem">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>Shared HTTP cache is only available for anonymous users. Logged in users=
 will be served the same cache as for anonymous users, except for restricte=
d access.</p>
<p><strong>For personal information display, you must use sub-requests with=
 ESI or Hinclude</strong>. Sub-controller would not use cache or make the c=
ached response vary with Cookie (individual cache).</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">eZ Publish uses <=
/span><a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/http_cache.html" style=
=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"=
nofollow">Symfony HttpCache</a><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height=
: 13.0pt;"> to manage content cache, with both </span><a href=3D"http://sym=
fony.com/doc/current/book/http_cache.html#http-expiration-and-validation" s=
tyle=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">expiration and validation model</a><span style=3D"font-size: =
10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">.&nbsp;Hence an </span><strong style=3D"font-s=
ize: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">ETag</strong><span style=3D"font-size: 10=
.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"> is computed for every content/version and sent =
in the Http response. It is also possible to use expiration model to get li=
ghtning fast responses.</span></p>
<p>An additional <strong>X-Location-Id</strong> header is added in the resp=
onse for identification (see <a href=3D"/display/EZP51/Purge">cache purge d=
ocument</a>).</p>
<h2 id=3D"HttpCache-Configuration">Configuration</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        my_siteaccess:
            content:
                view_cache: true      # Activates HttpCache for content
                ttl_cache: true       # Activates expiration based HttpCach=
e for content (very fast)
                default_ttl: 60       # Number of seconds an Http response =
is valid in cache (if ttl_cache is true)</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"HttpCache-Makingyourcontrollercontentcacheaware">Making your cont=
roller content cache aware</h2>
<p>Sometimes you need that your controller's cache expires in the same time=
 than a specific content (i.e. <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/bo=
ok/http_cache.html#using-esi-in-symfony2" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"no=
follow">ESI sub-requests with <code>render</code> twig helper</a>, for a me=
nu for instance). To be able to do that, you just need to add <strong>X-Loc=
ation-Id</strong> header to the response object:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response;
&nbsp;
// In a controller
// &quot;Connects&quot; the response to location #123 and sets a max age (T=
TL) of 1 hour.
$response =3D new Response();
$response-&gt;headers-&gt;set( 'X-Location-Id', 123 );
$response-&gt;setSharedMaxAge( 3600 );</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
